
msgid "Module *cartridge.failover*"
msgstr ""

msgid "Gather information regarding instances leadership."
msgstr ""

msgid "Failover can operate in two modes:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"In `disabled` mode the leader is the first server configured in "
"``topology.replicasets[].master``  array."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"In  ``eventual``  mode the leader isn't elected consistently. Instead, "
"every instance in cluster thinks the leader is the first **healthy** "
"server in replicaset, while instance health is determined according to "
"membership status (the SWIM protocol)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"In `stateful` mode leaders appointments are polled from the external "
"storage. (**Added** in v2.0.2-2)"
msgstr ""

msgid "This module behavior depends on the instance state."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"From the very beginning it reports `is_rw() == false`, ``is_leader() == "
"false`` ,  ``get_active_leaders() == {}`` ."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The module is configured when the instance enters `ConfiguringRoles` "
"state for the first time. From that moment it reports actual values "
"according to the mode set in clusterwide config."
msgstr ""

msgid "(**Added** in v1.2.0-17)"
msgstr ""

